{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cd1dd69e-bec9-4b2c-816c-57529804bf9f","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory. Since this is a general guidance question, here's what you need to change:\n\n### Switching to NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. NuGet.org setup:**\n- Go to **NuGet.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a new GitHub Actions publisher policy, specifying your **repo owner**, **repo name**, **workflow file name**, and optionally an **environment name**\n\n**2. Workflow changes:**\n\nAdd `id-token: write` permission and remove the API key:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: nuget-publish  # optional but recommended\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # required for OIDC\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      # Replace:\n      #   dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n      # With:\n      - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` in `--api-key` | Remove `--api-key` entirely |\n| No `permissions` block needed | Add `id-token: write` |\n| No environment needed | Add `environment:` (recommended) |\n\n**3. Cleanup:**\n- Delete the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo/org settings once the new flow works.\n\nThe OIDC token is automatically exchanged with NuGet.org — no secrets required. Want me to modify your actual workflow file if you point me to it?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8efa51bf-4193-4e2f-93c1-232505d3572c","outputTokens":486},"id":"eb3057c9-d8c5-49f0-9a4f-e5ca1fc4cd15","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:39:31.171Z","parentId":"d99fe441-694d-4330-8bfb-0c2cb8b30085"}
